15/10/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The trial against Branimir Glavas and six other people begins in Zagreb County Court on Monday (October 15th). 
The seven defendants, who have repeatedly staged hunger strikes, are charged with war crimes committed in the eastern Croatian Osijek region in 1991, including the torture and murder of ten ethnic Serb civilians. 
An estimated 250 witnesses are to testify in the case. 
(RTRS, SRNA - 15/10/07)
